cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Carnaval: a reversible PII anonymization framework"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: AUBERT
    given-names: Patrice
repository-code: "https://github.com/carnaval-ai/carnaval"
abstract: >-
  Carnaval is an open-source Python framework for reversible PII
  anonymization. It masks sensitive entities in text documents before
  they are sent to a cloud LLM, then restores the original values in the
  structured response, using a local AES-256-GCM encrypted vault.
keywords:
  - pii
  - anonymization
  - privacy
  - gdpr
  - nlp
  - named-entity-recognition
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-05-16
identifiers:
